HashMap implementation

Internally Hashmap consists of array of buckets and buckets size is fixed and changes dynamically
 if the more keys are added:

bucket[0]
bucket[1]
bucket[2]
bucket[3]
...
bucket[n-1]

size=1000 (size of the buckets)

How key is placed in the Bucket?

index= keys % size

at bucket[index], we just insert key and value in the form of linkedlist
If multiple keys are mapped to the same bucket then collision happens which led to linkedlist chaining

Load factor: How full the hashmap is
Rehashing : When the Hashmap is full then we increase the size of the bucket

implementation of HashSet is also very similar, The difference is that the node class have only key

